    <h2 id="what-is-l-theanine">What L-Theanine Does to Your Brain in 40 Minutes</h2>

    <p>L-theanine (gamma-glutamylethylamide) is a non-protein amino acid found almost exclusively in the <em>Camellia sinensis</em> tea plant. It is the compound responsible for why green tea produces a qualitatively different alertness than coffee — calm and focused rather than jittery and anxious. When ingested, L-theanine crosses the blood-brain barrier within 30 to 40 minutes and produces measurable neurological effects that have been documented in over 40 peer-reviewed studies.</p>

