    <!-- FAQ SECTION -->
    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About L-Theanine Gummies</h2>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What does L-theanine do?</summary>
      <p>L-theanine is an amino acid found in green tea that crosses the blood-brain barrier and increases alpha brain wave activity within 30 to 40 minutes. Alpha waves are associated with calm alertness. L-theanine also increases GABA, serotonin, and dopamine levels. A 2008 study in <em>Nutritional Neuroscience</em> confirmed that 200mg significantly increased alpha waves in healthy adults, producing relaxation without sedation.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>How much L-theanine should I take?</summary>
      <p>Clinical studies show effects at 100 to 400mg daily. For calm focus, 200mg is the standard effective dose. For sleep support, 200 to 400mg before bedtime is commonly used. L-theanine is FDA GRAS with no known toxicity ceiling. The Suntheanine brand guarantees 100% pure L-isomer for maximum bioactivity.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Does L-theanine make you sleepy?</summary>
      <p>No. L-theanine promotes relaxation without sedation. The alpha brain waves it produces are associated with calm alertness, similar to meditation. It can be taken during the day for focus without impairing cognition or causing drowsiness. When taken before bed, it supports sleep quality by reducing anxiety — not by directly inducing sleep.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Can I take L-theanine with caffeine?</summary>
      <p>Yes, this is one of the most documented nootropic combinations. L-theanine + caffeine produces focused energy without jitters. A 2008 study found the combination improved attention accuracy and reduced distraction susceptibility. The optimal ratio is approximately 2:1 (L-theanine to caffeine) — 200mg L-theanine with 100mg caffeine.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Is L-theanine safe to take every day?</summary>
      <p>Yes. L-theanine is FDA Generally Recognized as Safe (GRAS) with no known toxicity ceiling at supplemental doses. Clinical trials have used up to 400mg daily for extended periods without adverse effects. It does not cause dependence, tolerance, or withdrawal symptoms.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What is Suntheanine and why does it matter?</summary>
      <p>Suntheanine is a patented, pure L-isomer form of theanine produced through enzymatic fermentation. Generic L-theanine may contain a mixture of L-theanine and D-theanine isomers — only the L-isomer is bioactive. Suntheanine guarantees 100% pure L-theanine with over 40 published studies supporting its efficacy.</p>
    </details>

